 </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukathartic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kathartic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(9/20/02 5:18:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=328.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   teamwork?</span><hr size=1> I can see the point of folks tired of popping out mod rods.  However prior to that, coh and focus items what was our purpose on a raid?  We were just &quot;damage&quot; and weren't needed.  At least we now have some things that are needed in a raid.  <br>
<br>
Someone playing any class would likely find the same thing in a raid situation.  &quot;All I ever do is xxxx&quot;.  If that's what you do, just do it well.  As was said, it's about teamwork and specialization.  <br>
